{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"112b4d8d-8366-4177-9d16-149b8074bf28","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's what to watch for:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for .NET Core targets.\n- **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL). You need at least **`net6.0`**.\n- **`net462`** — still supported ✅ (minimum is .NET Framework 4.6.2).\n\n**Package changes in MSTest v3:**\nThe separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n1. Update `TargetFrameworks` — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` (or later).\n2. Replace the two MSTest package references with a single `MSTest` package (v3.x).\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a655750-c71a-43db-b45d-9f1804a334bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 key changes:\n- Minimum supported frameworks: .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported (it's EOL and MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported (MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `net462` should still be supported (MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\n\n- MSTest v3 also consolidates into a single `MSTest` meta-package rather than separate framework and adapter packages, which simplifies the dependency structure.","outputTokens":483,"requestId":"E3C3:2C57B5:B0BE03:CA4D2E:6A053BDA"},"id":"56900437-cb7c-4b2e-8883-458599a46697","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:05:08.259Z","parentId":"e09b8705-9ba0-433d-ab10-444177e0075b"}
